  "market_context": "Bullish intraday trend on CL1! with higher lows and higher highs forming. Analyst observed price moving from internal range liquidity (hourly FVG) to external range liquidity, anticipating continuation. Occurred during Wednesday session with strong daily bias up.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed equal lows before retracing into a pre-identified hourly fair value gap (IRL), then confirmed a change in state of delivery on the 5-minute chart, enabling a continuation entry from a retested propulsion block/Order Block.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly chart, analyst identified an internal range liquidity zone (fair value gap) between ~67.30–67.35 and anticipated price would retrace into it to form a higher low.",
    "Step 2: Observed price making equal lows instead of immediately entering the FVG, then later retracing into the FVG zone (~67.30–67.35) as expected for a higher low formation.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 5-minute chart, located the swing low and the series of down-close candles that formed it, then marked the opening price of that series as the mean threshold for a potential CISD.",
    "Step 4: Waited for and identified a close above the opening price of the down-close series (CISD), confirming bullish change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 5: Took a continuation entry on retest of the propulsion block/Order Block (around 67.60–67.65), placing stop below the confirmed low and targeting 2R toward the next external range liquidity level.",
    "Step 6: Verified both initial and continuation entries hit 2R targets, with price progressing from internal to external liquidity in alignment with the uptrend structure."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both the initial entry and the continuation entry hit 2R profit targets successfully.",
  "lessons": "In a strong uptrend with higher lows, price often retraces into internal range liquidity (FVG) before continuing. A 5-minute CISD above the opening price of the prior swing’s down-close series validates the continuation, enabling high-probability entries at retested order blocks with tight risk.",
